Package gov.nasa.gsfc.nisgs.dsm

Class Summary
Attribute An attribute is a name and value pair to be stored in a subproduct table.
CopyMover Copies file between locations managed by the DSM.
DSM DSM is an interface class to the DSM subsystem and database.
DSMAdministrator DSMAdministrator is an interface class to the DSM subsystem and database.
DsmProperties This class holds DSM properties from many sources (local init files, database tables), courtesy of its superclass.
FileMover Abstract class that handles moving files from Site to Site (Site has its NISGS meaning here of machine/data-directory).
FtpISReader Fetches files from the IS via FTP.
FtpISWriter Writes files to the IS using FTP.
FtpMover Abstract class that moves files between locations managed by the DSM using FTP.
GCDatabase GCDatabase Cleans the database.
MarkerRef Little class that packages a marker reference (markerId, gopherColony) for convenient storage in containers.
NCSHelper This class serves as a scratchpad for NCS scripts.
Pass This class is one spacecraft pass.
Product This class contains all information related to one product in the DSM database.
ProductFactory ProductFactory creates a Product object from a database Product record.
ProductType A product type in the DSM database.
ProductTypes The job of this static class is handle anything to do with product types and the ProductTypes table in the database.
Reservation Reservation handles reserving and releasing products for the DSM.
Resource A resource is a container for a product resource or thumbnail.
Station A station in the DSM database.
TimeWindow This class packages up two time intervals, expressed as millisecond offsets from a presumed center time.
